\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line PC Training and  Business College is registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training and is accredited to offer higher education programmes by the HEQC.\line \line In the AC meeting of 28 and 29 July 2010\'2C the institution was requested to provide some clarity with regard to the following points in the application\'3A\line 1. The programme design should be re-curriculated as the present design does not meet the general characteristics of a Higher Certificate in Office Administration. The following aspects should be considered\'3A including a Typing\'2FComputer component\'2C replacing Cost and Management Accounting with Human Relations\'2C upgrading Bookkeeping to Business Finance\'2FAccounting and revising Business and Office Administration to include aspects such as general orientation into the profession\'3B personality traits required for office professionals\'3B basic rules of conduct and professional ethics\'3B time management\'2C etc.\line 2. The admission requirements of a National Senior Certificate with exposure to computer literacy \'28where necessary\'29 as an advantage is contradictory to the curriculum content which does not include any further training in Computing. This should be reconsidered in the light of the programme redesign.\line 3. The assessment strategies lack detail and require clarity in terms of the number and types of tests\'2Fassignments\'2Fprojects\'2Fcase studies\'3B formative and integrated assessment exercises\'3B a record of students\'E2\'80\'99 performance\'2C problem areas identified and improvement plans\'3B examiners and moderators\'E2\'80\'99 reports and what measures have been taken to incorporate those into teaching and learning.\line 4. Although a list of prescribed books is provided for each module offered in this programme\'2C the institution should identify library resources specifically earmarked for this programme\'2C indicating how the theory \'2F taught aspects of the programme are linked to the independent resource aspects and how the institution\'E2\'80\'99s information resources support these aspects.  \line 5. Applications for new programmes will only be considered for the following sites of delivery. Should the institution wish to offer on additional sites of delivery\'2C individual applications for each site of delivery will need to be made\line 1. 292 Smith Street\'2C Durban\'2C 4000\line 2. 32 Diagonal Street\'2C Cnr Sauer \'26 Jeppe\'2C Johannesburg\line 3. 13 Church Street\'2C Pretoria\line 4. 22A Aliwal Street\'2C Cnr Elizabeth \'26 Aliwal Street\'2C  Bloemfontein\line 5. 49 St George Mall\'2C Cnr Castle Street  \'26 St George Mall\'2C Cape Town\line 6. 235 Langalibalele Street\'2C Pietermaritzburg\line 7. Voortrekker Street\'2C Kempton Park\line 8. 141 Main Street\'2C Johannesburg\line 9. 52 Joe Slovo \'28Field\'29 Street\'2C Durban\line \cell \pard 

