\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator stated that most of the concerns raised were addressed in the additional information provided. It would appear that the institution has re-curriculated the programme attending to the majority of issues raised. \line \line In terms of Criterion 2 the evaluator suggrests that the issue of flooding the market is of concern in some of the cities.  For example\'2C there are more than two learning sites in Pretoria\'2C Braamfontein and Johannesburg.  It is recommended that the programme be offered at one learning site in these cities during its initial phases and be extended to others gradually.\line \line The concerns raised in the initial evaluation regarding staffing have not been adequately addressed.  The staff members have adequate qualifications \'28one-level higher\'29 and teaching experience \'282 to 4 years\'29.  These are however in the Business and Commercial field and not relevant to Office Administration.\line \line The Directorate does not support the recommendation that the programme should not be accredited. It recommends that the programme be accredited for the following sites of delivery\'3A\line \line 1. Smith Street\'2C Durban\'2C 4000\line 2. Jorrisen Street\'2C Braamfontein \'28replacing Diagonal Street\'2C Johannesburg\line 3. Struben Street\'2C Pretoria \'28replacing Church Street\'2C Pretoria\'29\line 4. Aliwal Street\'2C Cnr Elizabeth \'26 Aliwal Street\'2C  Bloemfontein\line 5. St George Mall\'2C Cnr Castle Street  \'26 St George Mall\'2C Cape Town\line 6. Longmarket \'28Langalibalele\'29 Street\'2C Pietermaritzburg\line 7. Voortrekker Street\'2C Kempton Park\line 8. Main Street\'2C Johannesburg\line 9. Joe Slovo \'28Field\'29 Street\'2C Durban \line Should the institution wish to offer additional sites of delivery\'2C individual applications for each site of delivery will need to be made.\line \cell \pard 

